<i>adverb</i>: 흔히 [흔히], 평범히 [평범히], 통상 [통상], 주로 [주로], 예사로 [예ː사로], 보통 [보ː통], 대개 [대ː개] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>흔히 [흔히]</dt><br>
<dd>often; commonly; usually</dd><br>
<dd>보통보다 더 자주.</dd><br>
<dd>More often than usual.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>평범히 [평범히]</dt><br>
<dd>ordinarily; usually; commonly</dd><br>
<dd>뛰어나거나 특별한 점이 없이 보통으로.</dd><br>
<dd>In an ordinary state, with nothing excellent or special.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>통상 [통상]</dt><br>
<dd>usually; in general</dd><br>
<dd>일상적으로. 또는 일반적으로.</dd><br>
<dd>Ordinarily, or generally.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>주로 [주로]</dt><br>
<dd>usually</dd><br>
<dd>기본이나 중심이 되게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of serving as a basis or center.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>예사로 [예ː사로]</dt><br>
<dd>1. usually; easily</dd><br>
<dd>보통 일처럼 아무렇지도 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of making nothing of doing something as if it was nothing special.</dd><br>
<dd>2. as an ordinary thing</dd><br>
<dd>그저 그만하게.</dd><br>
<dd>As a common thing.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>보통 [보ː통]</dt><br>
<dd>usually; in general</dd><br>
<dd>일반적으로. 또는 흔히.</dd><br>
<dd>Generally, or normally.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>대개 [대ː개]</dt><br>
<dd>generally; usually</dd><br>
<dd>일반적으로.</dd><br>
<dd>In general.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>